# F1D Project - Technical Reference

## Project Description

This project processes earnings call transcripts to generate linguistic measures based on the Loughran-McDonald (LM) dictionary and estimate CEO communication styles. It extracts speech by speaker role and context, tokenizes text, counts dictionary matches, links results to CRSP-Compustat Merged (CCM) database with Fama-French industry classifications, and estimates CEO fixed effects to measure persistent communication clarity.

**Data scope**: 17 years (2002-2018)
**Input data**: Speaker-level earnings call transcripts
**Output data**:
- Call-level linguistic measures (4 measures per call)
- Financial control variables (stock returns, EPS growth, earnings surprises)
- CEO Clarity scores (persistent communication style for 3,306 CEOs)
- CCM linkage and industry classifications

## Design Principles

This project follows strict architectural principles for reproducibility and maintainability:

- **Deterministic Execution**: Fixed seeds, pinned threads, stable sort orders ensure bitwise-identical outputs
- **No-Flags Execution**: All scripts read from `config/project.yaml` only—no command-line arguments required
- **Real Data Only**: No mock/synthetic data without explicit approval and documentation
- **Minimal Design**: KISS/YAGNI principles—avoid overengineering and unnecessary abstractions
- **Single Source of Truth**: Configuration centralized in `config/project.yaml`
- **Transparent Logging**: Dual-writer pattern outputs verbatim to both terminal and log files

For complete architectural guidelines, see `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.

